ca.cgjennings.ui

Interface BrowserPanel.LocationMapper

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BrowserPanel.DefaultLocationMapper
    Enclosing class:
    BrowserPanel

    public static interface BrowserPanel.LocationMapper
    Converts between values in the address bar and actual URLs; this allows you to use virtual addresses and map them to non-virtual URLs.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      URL addressToURL(String address)
      Convert the address to a URL, or return null if the address is invalid.
      String generateDocument(String address)
      This method is called before translating an address.
      String URLToAddress(URL url)
      Convert a URL back to an address, or return null if the URL cannot be mapped to an address

    • Method Detail

      • addressToURL

        URL addressToURL(String address)
        Convert the address to a URL, or return null if the address is invalid.
        Parameters:
        address - the address field value to convert
        Returns:
        the URL that the address maps to, or null

      • generateDocument

        String generateDocument(String address)
        This method is called before translating an address. If it returns a non-null value, that value will be used as the document text for the page instead of loading a URL.
        Parameters:
        address - the address to generate a document for
        Returns:
        the document text, or null to translate the address to a URL and attempt to load it

      • URLToAddress

        String URLToAddress(URL url)
        Convert a URL back to an address, or return null if the URL cannot be mapped to an address
        Parameters:
        url - the URL to map to an address
        Returns:
        the address that the URL maps to, or null
